By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   The Federal Capital Territory Tuesday led the COVID-19 table with 416 infections as Nigeria recorded 999 new cases of the novel virus, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. The NCDC in its report released via twitter handle said Lagos State came second with 324 while Kaduna and Plateau came third and fourth with 68 and 42 infections respectively. Others are; Kwara-32, Kano-24, Gombe-14,Sokoto and Yobe-12 each, Akwa Ibom-11, Bayelsa-10, Rivers and Bauchi-7 each, Ogun-6, Oyo-5, Edo and Taraba-4 each and Jigawa-1. According to the health agency, the total confirmed cases have risen to 79,789 out of which 68,879 have been discharged. The health agency further informed that1,231 deaths have been recorded since the index case was reported in February 27. The states breakdown of total confirmed cases is given below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The total confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Nigeria hit 59,001 as the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported 153 new fresh infections on Thursday. Similarly, the NCDC report released via it's twitter handle account further said that the total of 50, 452… October 2, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Tuesday confirmed 137 new cases of COVID-19 Nigeria. The report released by the health agency via it's twitter handle stated that Lagos state, the epicentre of the novel virus infection led the table with 60 fresh… November 4, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Precise Post) -   The national health agency in charge of COVID-19, Nigeria Centre for  Disease Control on Tuesday announced the confirmation of 296 new cases of the novel virus in the country. The agency reported that the new infections were recorded in 15 states of the… September 9, 2020 In "Top Stories"